SORTSMILL-CHANGELOGGER(1)        User Commands       SORTSMILL-CHANGELOGGER(1)



NAME
       sortsmill-changelogger - Sorts Mill Changelogger

SYNOPSIS
       sortsmill-changelogger [IGNORED]... [OPTION]...

DESCRIPTION
       Create a GNU-style ChangeLog file from a version control log.

       -C DIR change to repository base directory DIR

       -l ENTRIES
              limit the number of changes displayed

       -h     display this help and exit

       -V     output version information and exit

       The optional arguments `IGNORED' are ignored.

       Unless you use the -C flag, sortsmill-changelogger expects to be run in
       a repository's base directory.

       The environment variable SORTSMILL_HG_LOG_STYLE can be used to specify
       an alternative Mercurial log style.

       The environment variable SORTSMILL_GIT_LOG_PROCESSOR can be used to
       specify an alternative git log processor.

AUTHOR
       Written by Barry Schwartz.

